The paper discusses the sTeX+ system, which is a semantic extension of LaTeX used as a formalization tool in a software engineering case study. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Software Engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Linked Data and RDFa, which are topics related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper also discusses the preservation of structural annotations for semantic information retrieval, which is a topic related to Data Mining (cs.DL).
